cfcGenericGlobalFabConfigMode.name: cfcGenericGlobalFabConfigMode
cfcGenericGlobalFabConfigMode.description: This object gives the current bandwidth and redundancy configuration of fabric in the system.

cfcGenericGlobalFabMasterSched.name: cfcGenericGlobalFabMasterSched
cfcGenericGlobalFabMasterSched.description: This object gives the entPhysicalIndex of the master scheduler fabric card in the system. If there is no master scheduler card then this object will return the value zero.

cfcGenericFabToFabTable.name: cfcGenericFabToFabTable
cfcGenericFabToFabTable.description: A table providing ToFabFIA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcGenericFabToFabEntry.name: cfcGenericFabToFabEntry
cfcGenericFabToFabEntry.description: An entry providing various ToFabFIA statistics and information of the associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcGenericFabToFabState.name: cfcGenericFabToFabState
cfcGenericFabToFabState.description: Indicates the current state of the ToFabFIA. active - ToFabFIA is currently active. On reaching a test point for the FIA errors, the ToFabFIA will be moved to halted state.

cfcGenericFabToFabGrantPEs.name: cfcGenericFabToFabGrantPEs
cfcGenericFabToFabGrantPEs.description: Count of parity errors detected by the ToFabFIA on the grant lines to SCA.

cfcGenericFabToFabRequestPEs.name: cfcGenericFabToFabRequestPEs
cfcGenericFabToFabRequestPEs.description: Count of parity errors detected by the ToFabFIA on the request lines to SCA. These errors are detected by the SCA and fed back to the ToFabFIA.

cfcGenericFabToFabCellFifoPEs.name: cfcGenericFabToFabCellFifoPEs
cfcGenericFabToFabCellFifoPEs.description: Count of cell parity errors detected by the ToFabFIA while dequeuing cells from the cell fifo.

cfcGenericFabFrFabTable.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabTable
cfcGenericFabFrFabTable.description: A table providing FrFabFIA information in the managed system.

cfcGenericFabFrFabEntry.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabEntry
cfcGenericFabFrFabEntry.description: An entry providing FrFabFIA information of the associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcGenericFabFrFabState.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabState
cfcGenericFabFrFabState.description: Indicates the current state of the FrFabFIA. active - FrFabFIA is currently active. On reaching a test point for the FIA errors, the FrFabFIA will be moved to halted state

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliTable.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliTable
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliTable.description: A table providing per serial link information maintained by the FrFabFIA in the managed system.

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliEntry.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliEntry
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliEntry.description: An entry providing per serial link information maintained by the FrFabFIA on an associated linecard.

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the switch fabric cards (CSC/SFC) present in the monitored system.

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSErrors.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSErrors
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSErrors.description: Count of LOS errors detected by the FrFabFIA on the serial link to the fabric card identified by cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex.

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliCRCErrors.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliCRCErrors
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliCRCErrors.description: Count of CRC errors detected by the FrFabFIA on the serial link to the fabric card identified by cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex.

cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSState.name: cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSState
cfcGenericFabFrFabSliLOSState.description: State of LOS detection as enabled on FrFabFIA (identified by entPhysicalIndex) for the serial link to the switch fabric card identified by cfcGenericFabFrFabSliFabIndex. Value is either, (1) losOff (2) losOn A losOff state normally indicates that the FrFabFIA has detected a state of persisting LOS on the serial link and has disabled LOS detection for that serial link.

cfcGenericScaTable.name: cfcGenericScaTable
cfcGenericScaTable.description: A table providing SCA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcGenericScaEntry.name: cfcGenericScaEntry
cfcGenericScaEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of SCA on an associated CSC identified by the respective entPhysicalIndex.

cfcGenericScaIdentifier.name: cfcGenericScaIdentifier
cfcGenericScaIdentifier.description: The vendor-specific identifier string of SCA ASIC. This identifier generally includes the revision number and the manufacturing part number of SCA.

cfcGenericScaIntrStatus.name: cfcGenericScaIntrStatus
cfcGenericScaIntrStatus.description: Gives the status/occurrence of different alarm conditions in the SCA. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcGenericScaIntrsEnabled.name: cfcGenericScaIntrsEnabled
cfcGenericScaIntrsEnabled.description: Gives the list of different alarm conditions enabled to be generated by the SCA.

cfcGenericScaConfig.name: cfcGenericScaConfig
cfcGenericScaConfig.description: Gives the current configuration of the SCA ASIC. quarterBandwidth (0) -- 1/4th of the full bandwidth is supported per slot by the switch. halfBandwidth (1) -- 1/2th of the full bandwidth is supported per slot by the switch. fullBandwidth (2) -- Full bandwidth is supported per slot by the switch. enableParity (3) -- Parity handling by SCA is enabled. priMcast (4) -- Priority of Multicast requests is greater then Unicast requests. priUnicast (5) -- Priority of Unicast requests is greater then Multicast requests. priAlternating (6) -- Alternate the priority between pri-mcast and pri-unicast modes every cell clock. earlyIntrOnLOS (7) -- Cause early interrupt on loss-of-sync error. noEarlyIntrOnLOS (8) -- Allow time to resync on loss-of-sync error. forceXbarParityXer (9) -- Force bad parity on xbar on every cell clock. forceGrantParityXer (10) -- Force bad partity on grant to every line card. unicastAcceptMode (11) -- Enable unicast accept pointer updating only on cell periods when Unicast has higher priority over multicast. forceXbarCrcOnCtlLink0 (12)-- Force CRC error on Xbar control link 0. forceXbarCrcOnCtlLink0 (13)-- Force CRC error on Xbar control link 1. forceXbarCrcOnCtlLink0 (14)-- Force CRC error on Xbar control link 2. forceXbarCrcOnCtlLink0 (15)-- Force CRC error on Xbar control link 3.

cfcGenericScaPELog.name: cfcGenericScaPELog
cfcGenericScaPELog.description: Indicates the modules which caused the parity error and resulted in an interrupt. The corresponding bit is set on occurrence of parity error for a module. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcGenericScaFifoOverflowLog.name: cfcGenericScaFifoOverflowLog
cfcGenericScaFifoOverflowLog.description: Indicates the modules which caused an overflow at the request fifo and resulted in an interrupt. The corresponding bit is set on occurrence of fifo overflow for a module. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcGenericScaLCsEnabled.name: cfcGenericScaLCsEnabled
cfcGenericScaLCsEnabled.description: Indicates the modules which are present and the SCA has been configured to start accepting requests from this module.

cfcGenericScaForcedBackPressure.name: cfcGenericScaForcedBackPressure
cfcGenericScaForcedBackPressure.description: Indicates the linecards which exerted backpressure. SCA will not grant Xbar connection to these linecards.

cfcGenericScaOc192LCsPresent.name: cfcGenericScaOc192LCsPresent
cfcGenericScaOc192LCsPresent.description: Indicates the OC192 linecards present in the monitored system. The corresponding bit is set for each linecard present, indicating the postion.

cfcGenericScaPreOc192LCsPresent.name: cfcGenericScaPreOc192LCsPresent
cfcGenericScaPreOc192LCsPresent.description: Indicates the Pre-OC192 linecards present in the monitored system. The corresponding bit is set for each linecard present, indicating the position.

cfcGenericXbarTable.name: cfcGenericXbarTable
cfcGenericXbarTable.description: A table providing Xbar information in the managed system.

cfcGenericXbarEntry.name: cfcGenericXbarEntry
cfcGenericXbarEntry.description: An entry providing Xbar information on an associated fabric card identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcGenericXbarIdentifier.name: cfcGenericXbarIdentifier
cfcGenericXbarIdentifier.description: The vendor-specific identifier string of Xbar ASIC. This identifier generally includes the revision number and the manufacturing part number of Xbar.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabTable.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabTable
cfcPreOc192FabToFabTable.description: A table providing pre-OC192 ToFabFIA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabEntry.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabEntry
cfcPreOc192FabToFabEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and counters of pre-OC192 ToFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabScaLosts.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabScaLosts
cfcPreOc192FabToFabScaLosts.description: Indicates the number of times the ToFabFIA lost contact with SCA(scheduler controller Asic) on master CSC.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoOvFlws.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoOvFlws
cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoOvFlws.description: Count of unicast fifo overflow errors on the ToFabFIA. Problems between BMA/CSAR and the ToFabFIA may be one of the reasons for these errors.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoUnFlws.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoUnFlws
cfcPreOc192FabToFabUCFifoUnFlws.description: Count of unicast fifo underflow errors on the ToFabFIA. These errors are caused by the SCA granting without actually getting a request from the ToFabFIA.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabMCFifoErrs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabMCFifoErrs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabMCFifoErrs.description: Count of multicast fifo overflow and underflow errors on the ToFabFIA. Problems between BMA/CSAR and the ToFabFIA may be one of the reasons for multicast fifo overflow errors. Underflow errors are caused by the SCA granting without actually getting a request from the ToFabFIA.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaPEs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaPEs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaPEs.description: Count of parity errors on cells received from BMA by the ToFabFIA.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaHskErrs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaHskErrs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabBmaHskErrs.description: Count of handshake errors between the BMA/CSAR and the ToFabFIA.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabUniDestMCRqs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabUniDestMCRqs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabUniDestMCRqs.description: Count of requests with single destination in a multicast request detected by ToFabFIA. The FIA will send this cell to the destination.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabMultiDstUCRqs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabMultiDstUCRqs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabMultiDstUCRqs.description: Count of requests with multiple destinations in a unicast request detected by a ToFabFIA. The FIA will drop this cell.

cfcPreOc192FabToFabEmptyDestRqs.name: cfcPreOc192FabToFabEmptyDestRqs
cfcPreOc192FabToFabEmptyDestRqs.description: Count of requests with empty destination detected by ToFabFIA. The FIA will drop this cell.

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabTable.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabTable
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabTable.description: A table providing pre-OC192 FrFabFIA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabEntry.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabEntry
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of pre-OC192 FrFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellFifoPEs.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellFifoPEs
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellFifoPEs.description: Count of cisco cell fifo parity errors detected by the FrFabFIA while dequeuing cells from the cell fifo.

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoPEs.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoPEs
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoPEs.description: Count of redundant data fifo parity errors detected by the FrFabFIA.

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoOvflws.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoOvflws
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabRedFifoOvflws.description: Count of redundant data fifo overflow errors detected by the FrFabFIA. This is caused if the back pressure is broken (i.e. the FrFabFIA exerts back pressure and the SCA keeps giving more data to it).

cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellDrops.name: cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellDrops
cfcPreOc192FabFrFabCellDrops.description: Count of number of cells dropped by the FrFabFIA. In case of non-redundant fabric configuration, cell drops can occur when a parity error is detected on one or more than one serial link. In case of redundant fabric configuration cell drops can occur when a cell gets corrupted on more than one serial link.

cfcPreOc192ScaTable.name: cfcPreOc192ScaTable
cfcPreOc192ScaTable.description: A table providing pre-OC192 SCA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcPreOc192ScaEntry.name: cfcPreOc192ScaEntry
cfcPreOc192ScaEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of pre-OC192 SCA on an associated CSC identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcPreOc192ScaReSyncDelay.name: cfcPreOc192ScaReSyncDelay
cfcPreOc192ScaReSyncDelay.description: The number of cell periods that the SCA will allow the serial links connected to a module and Xbar to be resynced, if a loss-of-sync has occurred on the corresponding module. The value '0' indicates that on occurrence of LOS, the sca will only log the LOS event and do the scheduling for that module as normal.

cfcPreOc192ScaLOSLog.name: cfcPreOc192ScaLOSLog
cfcPreOc192ScaLOSLog.description: Indicates the LOS event occurrence on each linecard connected to this CSC. The corresponding bit is set on occurrence of LOS event on a line card. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcPreOc192XbarTable.name: cfcPreOc192XbarTable
cfcPreOc192XbarTable.description: A table providing Pre-OC192 Xbar statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcPreOc192XbarEntry.name: cfcPreOc192XbarEntry
cfcPreOc192XbarEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of Pre-OC192 Xbar on an associated fabric card identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcPreOc192XbarIntrStatus.name: cfcPreOc192XbarIntrStatus
cfcPreOc192XbarIntrStatus.description: Indicates the occurrence of different alarm conditions in Xbar. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcPreOc192XbarParityChkStatus.name: cfcPreOc192XbarParityChkStatus
cfcPreOc192XbarParityChkStatus.description: Indicates the parity check state in control data received from SCA to the Xbar. true(1) indicates that the parity check is enabled. false(2) indicates that the parity check is disabled.

cfcOc192FabToFabTable.name: cfcOc192FabToFabTable
cfcOc192FabToFabTable.description: A table providing OC192 ToFabFIA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcOc192FabToFabEntry.name: cfcOc192FabToFabEntry
cfcOc192FabToFabEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of OC192 ToFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192FabToFabMccDataPEs.name: cfcOc192FabToFabMccDataPEs
cfcOc192FabToFabMccDataPEs.description: Count of the parity errors on data lines from MCC to ToFabFIA. This error would cause the ToFabFIA to halt.

cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdPEs.name: cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdPEs
cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdPEs.description: Count of the parity errors on command lines from MCC to ToFabFIA. This error would cause the ToFabFIA to halt.

cfcOc192FabToFabBackPressurePEs.name: cfcOc192FabToFabBackPressurePEs
cfcOc192FabToFabBackPressurePEs.description: Count of the parity errors on back pressure line from FrFabFIA to ToFabFIA. This error would cause the ToFabFIA to halt.

cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoOvFlws.name: cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoOvFlws
cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoOvFlws.description: Count of the cell fifo overflow errors detected by the ToFabFIA. This error would cause the ToFabFIA to halt.

cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoUnFlws.name: cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoUnFlws
cfcOc192FabToFabCellFifoUnFlws.description: Count of the cell fifo underflow errors detected by the ToFabFIA. This error would cause the ToFabFIA to halt.

cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqEndErrs.name: cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqEndErrs
cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqEndErrs.description: Count of the illegal sequence of command errors where a middle or start command followed by a start command is received from MCC.

cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqStrErrs.name: cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqStrErrs
cfcOc192FabToFabMccCmdSeqStrErrs.description: Count of the illegal sequence of command errors where an end command followed by an end or middle command is received from MCC.

cfcOc192FabFrFabTable.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabTable
cfcOc192FabFrFabTable.description: A table providing FrFabFIA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcOc192FabFrFabEntry.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabEntry
cfcOc192FabFrFabEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of OC192 FrFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenErrs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenErrs
cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenErrs.description: Count of the packets (after reassembly from Cisco cells) which exceed the maximum permitted packet length of FrFabFIA. These packets will be dropped.

cfcOc192FabFrFabExtRamPEs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabExtRamPEs
cfcOc192FabFrFabExtRamPEs.description: Count of the parity errors detected in FrFabFIA's external SRAM.

cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenPEs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenPEs
cfcOc192FabFrFabPktLenPEs.description: Count of the parity errors detected in payload packet length field of the FrFabFIA's Payload Header SRAM.

cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrSramPEs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrSramPEs
cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrSramPEs.description: Count of the parity errors detected in payload header field of the FrFabFIA's Payload Header SRAM.

cfcOc192FabFrFabTxCtrlPEs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabTxCtrlPEs
cfcOc192FabFrFabTxCtrlPEs.description: Count of the parity errors detected on the Tx control bits of FrFabFIA.

cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrFifoOvFlws.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrFifoOvFlws
cfcOc192FabFrFabHdrFifoOvFlws.description: Count of the overflow errors in the FrFabFIA's reassembly fifos in the on-chip payload header SRAM.

cfcOc192FabFrFabExtSramOvFlws.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabExtSramOvFlws
cfcOc192FabFrFabExtSramOvFlws.description: Count of the overflow errors in the FrFabFIA's reassembly external SRAM's payload fifos.

cfcOc192FabFrFabFirstLastErrs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabFirstLastErrs
cfcOc192FabFrFabFirstLastErrs.description: Count of the First-Last errors detected by FrFabFIA's. If a first cell is received for a reassembly fifo, while an earlier packet in the same reassembly fifo is still waiting for its last cell, then it is called a First-Last Error.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSeqErrs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSeqErrs
cfcOc192FabFrFabSeqErrs.description: Count of the sequence errors detected by FrFabFIA in the cells received for reassembly. If a cell is received whose sequence number is not an unit increment from the previous cell of the same packet then it is a sequence error.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSliTable.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSliTable
cfcOc192FabFrFabSliTable.description: A table providing per serial link information maintained by the OC192 FrFabFIA in the managed system.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSliEntry.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSliEntry
cfcOc192FabFrFabSliEntry.description: An entry providing per serial link information maintained by the OC192 FrFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSliSwitchIndex.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSliSwitchIndex
cfcOc192FabFrFabSliSwitchIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the switch fabric cards (CSC/SFC) present in the monitored system.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSliXorErrs.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSliXorErrs
cfcOc192FabFrFabSliXorErrs.description: Count of the XOR check errors detected by FrFabFIA reassembly. The data paths are horizontally XORed and the result is expected to match the contents of the redundant path else it is counted as XOR error, this error applies only in redundant mode of fabric.

cfcOc192FabFrFabSliCellDrops.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabSliCellDrops
cfcOc192FabFrFabSliCellDrops.description: Count of the total cells dropped by the FrFabFIA from the fabric card due to uncorrectable errors. Uncorrectable errors are the errors other than CRC, LOS, Horizontal XOR and idle cell which cannot be corrected.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatTable.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatTable
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatTable.description: A table providing per module statistics information maintained by the OC192 FrFabFIA in the managed system.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatEntry.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatEntry
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatEntry.description: An entry providing per module statistics information maintained by the OC192 FrFabFIA on an associated linecard identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the Line card present in the monitored system.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCHiPktDrops.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCHiPktDrops
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCHiPktDrops.description: Count of Unicast high priority packets dropped, from source module indicated by cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCLoPktDrops.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCLoPktDrops
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatUCLoPktDrops.description: Count of Unicast low priority packets dropped, from source module indicated by cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCHiPktDrops.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCHiPktDrops
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCHiPktDrops.description: Count of Multicast high priority packets dropped, from source module indicated by cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.

cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCLoPktDrops.name: cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCLoPktDrops
cfcOc192FabFrFabStatMCLoPktDrops.description: Count of Multicast low priority packets dropped, from source module indicated by cfcOc192FabFrFabStatLCIndex.

cfcOc192ScaTable.name: cfcOc192ScaTable
cfcOc192ScaTable.description: A table providing OC192 SCA statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcOc192ScaEntry.name: cfcOc192ScaEntry
cfcOc192ScaEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of OC192 SCA on an associated CSC identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192ScaRotationPeriod.name: cfcOc192ScaRotationPeriod
cfcOc192ScaRotationPeriod.description: Determines the period of rotating the priority between Unicast and Multicast, in cell periods, when the SCA is configured with alternating priority mode. For example, if the value of this object is 63 then the priority will change every 64 cell periods, if the value is 0 then the priority will change every cell period.

cfcOc192ScaDisableGrants.name: cfcOc192ScaDisableGrants
cfcOc192ScaDisableGrants.description: Indicates the disable of grants by SCA to any requests coming from a specific module. The corresponding bit is set for each module.

cfcOc192XbarTable.name: cfcOc192XbarTable
cfcOc192XbarTable.description: A table providing OC192 Xbar statistics and information in the managed system.

cfcOc192XbarEntry.name: cfcOc192XbarEntry
cfcOc192XbarEntry.description: An entry providing various statistics and information of OC192 Xbar on an associated fabric card identified by entPhysicalIndex.

cfcOc192XbarCtrlLOSStatus.name: cfcOc192XbarCtrlLOSStatus
cfcOc192XbarCtrlLOSStatus.description: Indicates the occurrence of LOS errors on the control path of Xbar. frameLosErr (0) -- Frame LOS error. sliErrorOnControlLink0 (1) -- LOS detected on SLI control link 0. sliErrorOnControlLink1 (2) -- LOS detected on SLI control link 1. sliErrorOnControlLink2 (3) -- LOS detected on SLI control link 2. sliErrorOnControlLink3 (4) -- LOS detected on SLI control link 3. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcOc192XbarCtrlCRCErr.name: cfcOc192XbarCtrlCRCErr
cfcOc192XbarCtrlCRCErr.description: Indicates the occurrence of CRC error on any of the four control links. This object is a read-clear object, that is the value of the object is cleared on every read.

cfcNotifEnable.name: cfcNotifEnable
cfcNotifEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the notifications defined in the MIB. A false value will prevent the notifications in the MIB from being generated by the system.

ciscoFabricC12kMIBFabMasterSchCh.name: ciscoFabricC12kMIBFabMasterSchCh
ciscoFabricC12kMIBFabMasterSchCh.description: This notification is generated when master scheduler on the system changes. It typically indicates the switchover of the scheduler card. cfcGenericGlobalFabMasterSched represents the entPhysicalIndex of the new master scheduler card, while entPhysicalName represents the entity physical name of the card. The case of all scheduler cards going down would be represented by a value 0 for the cfcGenericGlobalFabMasterSched and noSuchInstance for the entPhysicalName.
